{2026VideoGameDemo_v1.0}
con _clkfreq = 300_000_000              'Set system clock to 300MHz
  'debug_baud = 2_000_000              'You probably do not need to adjust the Debug baud rate at which the P2 and your PC communicate over their serial interface from its default value of 2 million bits per second. This commented-out line is included just in case you need to change this.
  'debug_delay = 500                   'You may find you need to add this 1/2 second wait before sending data to the PC's Debug window (in case your PC is slow and needs time to catch up and open the plot window before the P2 starts sending data to it)

  RJoyXMin=4, RJoyXMax=252, RJoyYMin=4, RJoyYMax=252, LJoyXMin=2, LJoyXMax=254, LJoyYMin=4, LJoyYMax=252 'Your Wii Controller probably uses these default range values, but not all of them have been tested. You can use the Wii Controller Tester program to verify exactly what values your controller outputs
  #0, x, y, width, height             '#0 resets the automatic constant counter number to 0 (just in case it has been changed by preceding unspecified constants), so here x=0, y=1, width=2, height=3 which is convenient for collision definitions arrays e.g., Momot[x] is the same as Momot[0], Momot[y] is the same as Momot[1], etc. (and for most people, it's easier to remember that the x index holds the x position value rather than the 0th index holds the x value!-)

  FrameTime=100                        'Set your target frame duration/period in milliseconds (i.e., frame rate). This value should probably be between around 50-100ms, i.e. the screen should be cleared and completely redrawn every 50-100ms. If you set your frame rate/frequency too high (i.e., set this FrameTime/period value too low) and don't have at least around 15ms of pause time between each loop, then the USB interface through which the P2 talks to your computer may get clobberred and bogged down, which can result in strange behavior such as the controller data seeming to lag way behind, appearing to make characters move on their own or long after the controls were pressed.
  CollisionDebugMode=false            'Setting this to be true draws red boxes around all entities that are checked for collisions, but doing this can significant slow down your main loop. Therefore, only enable this feature for a brief time while debugging specific problems i.e., don't keep this active/true throughout your entire game making process!


  {PROPERTIES}

  {SPRITE NAMES}
  #100 'Explaining the above comment quickly; spin2 auto increments constants w/out definitions,
        'and the #n sets the incrementer at n
  {Momot (MM) Sprites}
  MM_I '[100]; Idle
  MMSTEP0,MMSTEP1,MMSTEP2  ' [101-103]; combine w/ MM_I for walk cycle

  MMSPLAY ' [104]; his legs are splayed
  MMCROUCH ' [105]; One knee down
  MMRISE ' [106]; he is ascending, men of galilee
  MMFLOAT ' [107]; midair crouch
  MM8 ' [108];
  MMFALL ' [109] ' coming back down to earth
        'Can be continued if desired
  {Garner (GG) Sprites} ' [#-#] inclusive; Explanation
  #0
  GGIC, GGIU, GGIUR, GGIR ' [0-3];Idle + eye movement (Center, up, up-right, right)
  GGTALK ' [4]Switch w/ GGIC
  GGWALK0, GGWALK1, GGWALK2 ' [5-7]Walk Cycle
  GGJUMP ' [8] Legs split
  GGINSTRUCT ' [9] He's leading w/ his left & his mouth is open
  GGKIDS0, GGKIDS1, GGKIDS2, GGKIDS3 ' [10-13] Looks like he's waving his arms shouting "lousy kids."
  ' Could also be a hurt animation.
  GGFLY, GGFLYSTRUCT '[14-15] Flying, Attacking (i.e. like instruct)
  GGLAND, GGFALL, GGCROUCH ' [16-18] self-explanatory
  GGCLIMB[2] ' [19-20] Think Mario on vine; facing away from the screen  Need to update
  PROPLR[4] ' [21-24] The hat         Need to update


obj
  sprites : "OliveiraKammauffSprites_v2"    'Include 112#methods from your external "YourNameSprites" object. Of course, you should change the "YourName" part to be your actual name (LastFirst) for your unique sprite data loading object. Both this external object and your game file will be needed to play your game (so be sure to submit both!).
  i2c[2]     : "jm_i2c"                  'Include methods from jm_i2c bus driver so that the Wii Controller can communicate with the P2 chip over an I2C interface

var                                   'Declare global variables in this block, which can all be read or changed by any of the eight cogs at any time
  byte data[16], dataP2[8]                       'These array of 8 bytes is used to store data sent to the P2 chip from the Wii Classic Controller Pro. Your game must include this variable delcaration along with the SetupController and ReadController methods.
  long MomotPos[4], BulletB[4],HealthBoost[4], GarnerPos[4]          'Use arrays of 4 longs like these to keep track of all of your characters' data:
                                                                                'upper-left pixel's x-position, upper-left pixel's y-position, overall width, overall height.

  {Player Arrays and Variables:
  playerPos -> Player Position and Size
  playerState -> Records What the Player is Doing (Jumping, Blocking, Attacking, etc.)
  HitBoxes -> Store the Collision Areas for How Players Take Damage
  playerz -> Used for the "Gravity" Effect of Jumping
  HealthBar -> Stores Current Player Health
  Garner + Momot -> Control Which Sprite is Displayed for Them
  }
  long playerPos[8], playerState[18], HitBoxes[8], playerz[2], HealthBar[2], Momot, Garner

  {for playerState:
  [0] Sprite Number (unused), [1] Rotation, [2] Moving, [3] Opacity, [4] Jumping, [5] Punching/Throwing, [6] Kicking, [7] Blocking, [8] Hit}                                                                             'See the DefineCollisionAreas method below.


  {Position Arrays: Help Control Movement of Player and Interactions with the Controllers}

  long deltax[2], x_prev[2], y_prev[2], LJoyX[2], LJoyY[2], deltay[2] ' deltay deals only with jump speed
  long heightOffGround[2] ' Lets us know when they're landing

  long pvpState

  {Attack Arrays and Variables:
  PunchRight -> Variable Used to Alternate Momot's Base Attack Motion
  GGAtt -> Variable Used to Store Garner's Base Attack Sprite and Alternate It
  GGHAtt -> Variable Used to Store Garner's Heavy Attack Sprite and Alternate It
  GGBATT + GGHeATT -> Arrays used to Define Garner's Attack Collision Areas
  }
  long PunchRight, GGAtt, GGHAtt, GGBATT[4], GGHeATT[4]

  {Enemy Arrays and Variables:
  BulletHealth -> Stores Bullet Bill Health
  BulletRot -> Stores Bullet Bill Rotation
  PikminHealth -> Stores the Health Bars
  Pikmin -> Stores the Position and Collision Area For All Three Types of Pikmin
  }
  long BulletHealth, BulletRot, PikminHealth[3], Pikmin[12]

  {Game State Variables:
  KillCounter ->  Counts Enemies That Have Been Killed
  ActiveEnemies -> Keeps Track of How Many Enemies Are on the Screen
  HealthBoostGranted -> Keeps Track of If The HealthBoost Has Been Consumed
  CurrentLevel -> Tracks Current Level
  KillCounterCheck -> Keeps Track of the KillCounter Threshold that Finishes the Level
  RandomCheck -> Randomly Generated Number to Make the HealthBoost Spawn Random
  SpawnBoost -> HealthBoost Flag
  RPos -> Randomly Generated Position of HealthBoost
  Game Win + Lost -> Flags for if the game is won/lost
  }

  long KillCounter, ActiveEnemies, HealthBoostGranted, CurrentLevel, KillCounterCheck, RandomCheck, SpawnBoost,RPosX, RPosY, GameWon, GameLost
                                  '
  long FrameRate, FrameWaitTime, StartTime, RawLoopTime, LoopTime, DisplayDelay, Frame                              'These variables help to keep track of your game's frame rate i.e., how long it takes to run through your main game loop and redraw the screen
  'Create an empty array of 100 longs for each Cog
  'so that a Spin interpreter running on each has enough scratchpad RAM space
  'into which it can store temporary variables without accidentally overwriting other important data
  long Stack0[290], Stack1[100], Stack2[100], Stack3[100], Stack4[100], Stack5[5], Stack6[5], Stack7[100]

pub VideoGame() | i                 'This method runs on Cog 0 (which is what everything automatically starts running on by default)
  debug(`plot screen pos 100 0 size 768 640 backcolor black update) 'Create the main 768x640 pixel plot window for the game called "screen"
  debug(`screen set 400 330 blue text 50 'Loading sprites...')
  debug(`screen update)               'Refresh the screen in order to display the "Loading sprites" message. Note: You must always run an "update" command in order to actually see any changes you make to the debug data! In other words, calling other "debug" commands only changes the data for the next time that the screen is updated. Other debug commands do NOT automatically update the screen!!!
  SetupController(0)                   'Call the SetupController method to set up the I2C interface between the P2 and the 0th Wii Controller
  SetupController(1)                   'Call the SetupController method again, this time setting up Controller 1
  sprites.LoadSprites()               'Run the LoadSprites method from within your own Sprites object (a separate file) to upload all of your sprite data from the P2 chip's RAM into your PC's RAM
  debug(`screen clear update)         'Erase everything on the plot screen and update the screen (to erase the "Loading Sprites" text)
  ShowInstructions()                  'Display the instructions by overlaying a new debug text terminal over top of the video game's plot window



  cogspin(1, MomotMotion(),@Stack1)
  cogspin(2, GarnerMotion(),@Stack2)                       'Frame rate not good; run in main loop
  cogspin(3, EnemyMotion(),@Stack3)                'Start up Cog 1 and tell it to run the MarioMotion method in parallel to what's already running on Cog 0
  cogspin(4, PikminMotion(), @Stack4)
  cogspin(5, EasterEgg(), @Stack5)
  cogspin(7,DebugDisplay(),@Stack7)               'Start up Cog 7 and tell it to run the DebugDisplay method in parallel to what's going on on all of the other cogs (Note: You are not required to have this feature in your final game i.e., if you need to use Cog 7 for something else)
  SpawnActors()
  SpawnEnemies()
  DefineCollisionAreas()                           'Call the method that sets up the rectangles around objects that will be used to detect collisions
  if RandomCheck == 5
    SpawnBoost:=true
  CurrentLevel:=1                                 'Initializes game elements
  pvpState:=true
  repeat                                          'This is the game's main repeat loop. Ideally all debug plot/screen commands should be in this loop (and the methods it calls). So all debug plot/screen commands should only be called by Cog 0
    StartTime:=getct()                            'Record current system clock counter value to know when this iteration of the main game loop starts
    'debug(`screen clear)
    {Erase everything on the screen. Note: If you draw/redraw things over the entire screen
    (as the DrawBackground method does in this demo), then this statement is not necessary.
    You also may want to keep (i.e. not clear and redraw every frame) certain parts of your
    background that a character will never move on top of (to save time in each iteration of your main game loop)
     }

    {Draw the Game}
    DrawGame()

    {Get Controller Data}
    ReadController(0)
    ReadController(1)

    {Update Game State}

    if HealthBar[0] > 0      'Checks if the Player is still alive and if they are proceeds to check their different states'
      getPlayerState(1)       'Checks Player States'

    if HealthBar[1] > 0
      getPlayerState(2)

    if KillCounter > KillCounterCheck       'Checks If Enough Enemies Have Been Killed to Go to the Next Level'
      if CurrentLevel < 3                   'Levels Only go Up to 3'
        CurrentLevel := CurrentLevel + 1     'Go to Next Level'
        SpawnEnemies()                       'Reset Enemy Attributes to be Reused in the next level'
        KillCounter:=0                       'Reset Kill Counter'
        case_fast CurrentLevel               'Set New KillCounter Target'
          2 : KillCounterCheck:=12
          3 : KillCounterCheck:=22

    if KillCounter > KillCounterCheck  and CurrentLevel == 3     'Checks if all enemies in level 3 have been cleared'
      GameWon:=true                                                        'Win Screen'


    if HealthBar[0] < 0 and HealthBar[1] < 0                     'Checks if Both Players have lost all their health'
      GameLost:=true                                                  'Lose Screen'


                                                                  'Check whether or not the game has ended'
    if GameWon or GameLost
      if data[6].[2]==0                                            'Reset every enemy and player variable'
        SpawnActors()
        SpawnEnemies()
        DefineCollisionAreas()
        if RandomCheck == 5
          SpawnBoost:=true
        CurrentLevel:=1
        if GameWon                                                 'Set the game back to being playable by making the current end game condition false'
          GameWon:= false
        if GameLost
          GameLost:= false

    {Collision Checks:
    Defines Every Interaction Between Players, Enemies, and HealthBoost
    }

    if GameWon == false and GameLost == false
      if (CurrentLevel == 2 and HealthBoostGranted == false and SpawnBoost == true)   'May or may not spawn a HealthBoost at the beginning of level 2'
        if CheckCollision(@playerPos,@HealthBoost) and playerState[5]                 'Player must "collide" with the boost and use their base attack to collect it'
          HealthBar[0]:=(HealthBar + 72)                                               'Boost restores 72 health points (50% of HealthBar)'
          if HealthBar[0]>144                                                          'These statements make sure boost doesn't make the current health suprass the length og the healthbars'
           HealthBar[0]:=144
          HealthBoostGranted:=true
        if CheckCollision(@playerPos[4],@HealthBoost) and playerState[14]              'Same logic as above but for player 2'
            HealthBar[1]:=(HealthBar + 50)
          if HealthBar[1]>144
            HealthBar[1]:=144
          HealthBoostGranted:=true

      if(BulletHealth > 25 and CurrentLevel <> 2)                                    'Beacause enemy health is shown through opacity, enemy health checks
        if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes,@BulletB)                                          'don't go all the way down to 0, but instead 25'
          if playerState[7] == false                                                  'Check Enemy Health and because the Bullets are not in level 2, which level they are in'
            HealthBar[0]:=(HealthBar[0] - 1)                                         'Check Collision with Player Hitboxes'
        if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes[4],@BulletB)                                     'If colliding with a hitbox deal damage'
          if playerState[16] == false                                                 'If Blocking States are active Enemies do not deal damage'
             HealthBar[1]:=(HealthBar[1] - 2)

      if(BulletHealth > 25 and CurrentLevel <> 2)                                 'Is enemy alive check'
        if HealthBar[0] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@playerPos,@BulletB)                                  'Check Collision with Momot's offensive hitbox'
            if playerState[5]                                                     'Deal a certain amount of damage depending on which state player is in: Base or Heavy Attack'
              BulletHealth:=(BulletHealth - 15)                                   'Each attack deals a different amount of damage'
            if playerState[6]                                                     'For the Bullet Momot deals 15 HP for Base attack and 30 HP for heavy'
              BulletHealth:=(BulletHealth - 30)
        if HealthBar[1] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@GGBATT, @BulletB)                                    'Same checks for Garner except checks collisions with the lightning hitboxes'
            if playerState[14]                                                    'Heavy Attack Hit Box is smaller to balance both attacks'
              BulletHealth:=(BulletHealth - 10)
          if CheckCollision(@GGHeATT, @BulletB)
            if playerState[15]
              BulletHealth:=(BulletHealth - 40)

      if(PikminHealth[0] > 25)
        if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes,@Pikmin)
          if playerState[7] == false
            HealthBar[0]:=(HealthBar[0] - 3)
        if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes[4],@Pikmin)
          if playerState[16] == false
             HealthBar[1]:=(HealthBar[1] - 6)

      if(PikminHealth[0] > 25)
        if CheckCollision(@playerPos,@Pikmin)
          if playerState[5]
            PikminHealth[0]:=(PikminHealth[0] - 25)
          if playerState[6]
            PikminHealth[0]:=(PikminHealth[0] - 40)
        if CheckCollision(@GGBATT, @Pikmin)
          if playerState[14]
            PikminHealth[0]:=(PikminHealth[0] - 15)
        if CheckCollision(@GGHeATT, @Pikmin)
          if playerState[15]
            PikminHealth[0]:=(PikminHealth[0] - 50)



      if(PikminHealth[1] > 25)
        if HealthBar[0] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes,@Pikmin[4])
            if playerState[7] == false
              HealthBar[0]:=(HealthBar[0] - 2)
        if HealthBar[1] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes[4],@Pikmin[4])
            if playerState[16] == false
              HealthBar[1]:=(HealthBar[1] - 4)

      if(PikminHealth[1] > 25)
        if HealthBar[0] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@playerPos,@Pikmin[4])
            if playerState[5]
              PikminHealth[1]:=(PikminHealth[1] - 25)
            if playerState[6]
              PikminHealth[1]:=(PikminHealth[1] - 40)
        if HealthBar[1] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@GGBATT, @Pikmin[4])
            if playerState[14]
              PikminHealth[1]:=(PikminHealth[1] - 15)
          if CheckCollision(@GGHeATT, @Pikmin[4])
            if playerState[15]
              PikminHealth[1]:=(PikminHealth[1] - 50)


      if(PikminHealth[2] > 25)
        if HealthBar[0] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes,@Pikmin[8])
            if playerState[7] == false
              HealthBar[0]:=(HealthBar[0] - 2)
        if HealthBar[1] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes[4],@Pikmin[8])
            if playerState[16] == false
               HealthBar[1]:=(HealthBar[1] - 4)

      if(PikminHealth[2] > 25)
        if HealthBar[0] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@playerPos,@Pikmin[8])
            if playerState[5]
              PikminHealth[2]:=(PikminHealth[2] - 15)
            if playerState[6]
              PikminHealth[2]:=(PikminHealth[2] - 30)
        if HealthBar[1] > 0
          if CheckCollision(@GGBATT, @Pikmin[8])
            if playerState[14]
              PikminHealth[2]:=(PikminHealth[2] - 5)
          if CheckCollision(@GGHeATT, @Pikmin[8])
            if playerState[15]
              PikminHealth[2]:=(PikminHealth[2] - 35)

        {EASTER EGG-allow for pvp}
      if pvpState
        if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes,@GGBATT)
          if playerState[7] == false and playerState[5+9] == true 'GG basic attack
            HealthBar[0]:=(HealthBar[0] - 1)
        if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes[4],@playerPos)
          if playerState[16] == false and playerState[5] == true 'MM punch
             HealthBar[1]:=(HealthBar[1] - 15)
        if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes,@GGHeATT)
          if playerState[7] == false and playerState[6+9] == true 'GG heavy
            HealthBar[0]:=(HealthBar[0] - 2)
        if CheckCollision(@HitBoxes[4],@playerPos)
          if playerState[16] == false and playerState[6] == true 'MM heavy
            HealthBar[1]:=(HealthBar[1] - 30)

    ''It is highly recommended that you include the following code in your game
    Frame:=getct()
      FrameRate:=FrameTime*300_000 - abs(StartTime-Frame)   'Calculate the number of clock pulses remaining (that you need to pause for) to hit the target frame rate (specified by your FrameTime constant)
      if FrameRate<=0                                 'If the loop has taken more than the target frame time, display warning message. If you see this message, you need to increase the value of your FrameTime constant or decrease the amount of code (especially debug commands) running in your game's main repeat loop
        debug(`screen set 384 600 red text 20 'Frame loop took longer than 100ms!!!')              '
      waitct(FrameRate+getct())
      debug(`screen update)                           'Force game window to update then wait/delay 60ms Hint: Experiment with a delay of 0-100ms to get your total loop time (the time it takes to draw/redraw each frame/image) to be around 50-150 milliseconds. Just experiment with what works best for your final game to run smoothly.
      RawLoopTime:=abs(StartTime-getct())             'Record total loop time (not counting debug delay below) units=1/300_000_000=3.3333 nanoseconds


pub DebugDisplay()                                  'Use to display variables on the screen (Note: You could put this onto a separate cog if you need for your main game repeat loop on Cog 0 to run faster)
  debug(`term term1 pos 867 0 size 28 12 textsize 18 color cyan)    'Create terminal window to display variables to help with debugging or to display a score
  DisplayDelay:=clkfreq/5+getct()                   'Store a system clock "Tick" time that is 0.2 seconds in the future

  repeat
    LoopTime:=RawLoopTime*10/3000                   'Convert RawLoopTime (in units of system clock pulses) into microseconds
    FrameWaitTime:=FrameRate*10/3000                'Convert FrameRate (in units of system clock pulses) into microseconds. This should be
    if pollct(DisplayDelay)==true                   'Check to see if system counter has exceeded the DisplayDelay value
      'Erase everything on the terminal (text) window
      debug(`term1 clear)
      'Display any values that might be helpful when debugging, 10=New Line (so it creates a new line after printing)
      debug(`term1 'L Stick P1= `(data[0]) `(data[2])',10)
      debug(`term1 'R Stick P1 = `(data[1]) `(data[3])',10)

      debug(`term1 'L Stick P2= `(dataP2[0]) `(dataP2[2])',10)
      debug(`term1 'R Stick P2 = `(dataP2[1]) `(dataP2[3])',10)

      debug(`term1 'MomotJump: deltay:`(deltay[0]); height: `(heightOffGround)',10
      )
      debug(`term1 'LoopTime = `(LoopTime)' 'µs',10)
      debug(`term1 'Frame Wait Time = `(FrameWaitTime)' 'µs',10)

      DisplayDelay:=DisplayDelay+clkfreq/5          'Add another 0.2 second worth of system clock pulses to DisplayDelay time (for the next delay)

pub getPlayerState(player) | p, pos[4], i

    p:= player - 1

    deltax[p]:=abs(playerPos[x+4*p]-x_prev[p])                  'Difference between current x and previous x position (how far character has moved since last main loop iteration)
    x_prev[p]:=playerPos[x+4*p]                              'Store p's previous x position
    y_prev[p]:=playerPos[y+4*p]                              'Store p's previous y position

    'add the deltay value to the height off ground
    heightOffGround[p]:=0#> heightOffGround[p] + deltay[p]<#640
    {
    'Check the 4th bit of the 6th data byte from the controller, which is the -/select button.
    'If it is pressed (=0 in inverted logic), then call the GamePause method to pause the game
    if d[6].[4]==0
      PauseGame(p)
    }
    LJoyX[p]:=0#>(data[0+8*p]-LJoyXMin)*100/(LJoyXMax-LJoyXMin)<#100   'Scale the left joystick's analog X and Y ranges to be between 0-100
    LJoyY[p]:=0#>(data[2+8*p]-LJoyYMin)*100/(LJoyYMax-LJoyYMin)<#100   'Note that enclosing a computation or result between #> and <# in Spin2 limits the minimum and maximum value (in this case to beween 0 and 100)

    case_fast LJoyX[p]
       0..20  : playerPos[x+4*p]:=0#> playerPos[x+4*p]-16 <#740           'Same logic as Video Game Demo'
      21..30  : playerPos[x+4*p]:=0#> playerPos[x+4*p]-8 <#740
      31..40  : playerPos[x+4*p]:=0#> playerPos[x+4*p]-4 <#740
      61..70  : playerPos[x+4*p]:=0#> playerPos[x+4*p]+4 <#740
      71..80  : playerPos[x+4*p]:=0#> playerPos[x+4*p]+8 <#740
      81..100 : playerPos[x+4*p]:=0#> playerPos[x+4*p]+16 <#740

    case_fast LJoyY[p]                                                     'Vertical limit set to 312 to emulate the "2.5D" effect of the game'
      0..20  : playerz[p]:=64#> playerz[p]-16 <#312
      21..30  : playerz[p]:=64#> playerz[p]-8 <#312
      31..40  : playerz[p]:=64#> playerz[p]-4 <#312
      61..70  : playerz[p]:=64#> playerz[p]+4 <#312
      71..80  : playerz[p]:=64#> playerz[p]+8 <#312
      81..100 : playerz[p]:=64#> playerz[p]+16 <#312


    {Offset the PlayerPosY by height off the ground (make gravity jump effect)}

    playerPos[y+4*p]:= heightOffGround[p] + playerz[p]

    {Set hurtbox to the corresponing playerPos}

    HitBoxes[x+4*p]:= playerPos[x+4*p]+16
    HitBoxes[y+4*p]:= playerPos[y+4*p]


    {Player Pivoting}
    if playerPos[x+4*p]<>x_prev[p] or playerPos[y+4*p]<>y_prev[p]    'Making sure Motion methods are activated when the players move horizontally and vertically'
      playerState[2+9*p]:=true            'moving state                'Activate Moving state if X or Y position change'
      if playerPos[x+4*p]>x_prev[p]
        playerState[1+9*p]:=0             'rotation state              'Activate Pivot rotation state of X position is less than previous'
      elseif playerPos[x+4*p]<x_prev[p]
        playerState[1+9*p]:=1
        playerState[2+9*p]:=true
    else
      playerState[2+9*p]:=false


    {Player Jumping}
    if (data[7+8*p].[6] == 0) and (playerState[4+9*p] == false)       'state[4] is the jumping state
      playerState[4+9*p] := true                             '       CREDIT: Gemini -- AI Helped with the Jumping Logic, specifically on how to make it one motion with one press of B'

    {Player Basic Attack}

    if (data[7+8*p].[5] == 0) and (playerState[5+9*p] == false)       'playerState[5] is the attack state
      playerState[5+9*p] := true                                      'Active base attack state when Y is pressed'
      case_fast p
        0 : playerState[0] := 100            'spriteState'
        1 : playerState[9] := 0


    if playerState[5+9*p]
      case_fast p                                                      'Call specific base attack method'
        0 : MomotPunch()
        1 : GarnerBaseAttack()
      waitms(50#> 600/deltax[p] <#333)

    {Player Heavy Attack}

    if (data[7+8*p].[3] == 0) and (playerState[6+9*p] == false)       'playerState[6] is the heavy attack state
      playerState[6+9*p] := true                                       'Active heavy attack state when X is pressed'
      case_fast p
        0 : playerState[0] := 100            'spriteState'
        1 : playerState[9] := 0


    if playerState[6+9*p]                                               'Call specific heavy attack method'
      case_fast p
        0 : MomotKick()
        1 : GarnerHeavyAttack()
      waitms(50#> 600/deltax[p] <#333)

    {Player Block}

    if (data[7+8*p].[4] == 0) and (playerState[7+9*p] == false)       'playerState[7] is the block state
      playerState[7+9*p] := true                                       'Active block state when A is pressed'
      case_fast p
        0 : playerState[0] := 100            'spriteState'
        1 : playerState[9] := 0

    if playerState[7+9*p]
      case_fast p                                                    'Call specific block method'
        0 : MomotBlock()
        1 : GarnerBlock()

   {Garner Attack Hitboxes}
    if p == 1                                                        'Update Garner's Attack HitBoxes to match his position and rotation'
     case_fast playerState[10]
       0:
        GGBATT[x]:=playerPos[x+4*p]+80
        GGBATT[y]:=playerPos[y+4*p]-48
        GGHeATT[x]:=playerPos[x+4*p]+80
        GGHeATT[y]:=playerPos[y+4*p]-48
       1:
        GGBATT[x]:=playerPos[x+4*p]-64
        GGBATT[y]:=playerPos[y+4*p]-48
        GGHeATT[x]:=playerPos[x+4*p]-64
        GGHeATT[y]:=playerPos[y+4*p]-48

pub MomotMotion() | p
{Handle the physics, behavior, and sprite logic for Momot}
p:=0
  repeat

    if playerState[4+9*p] ' Jumping
      case_fast p
        0 : MomotJump()
        1 : GarnerJump()

    if playerState[2+9*p]==false
      {Idle State}
      Momot:= MM_I

    repeat until playerState[2+9*p]==true

    if playerState[2+9*p]==true
    {Moving animation}
        case Momot                              'Run through Momot's moving sprites'
          MM_I : Momot:= MMSTEP0
          MMSTEP0 : Momot:= MMSTEP1
          MMSTEP1 : Momot:= MMSTEP2
          MMSTEP2 : Momot:= MM_I
        waitms(FrameTime#> 6*FrameTime/deltax[p] <#4*FrameTime)

pub MomotJump() | p
'deals with the Momot Jumping animation and speed
  p:= 0 'For Momot
  Momot:= MMCROUCH
  waitms(1*FrameTime) 'Jumpsquat time
  'if {short vs. full hop; read button again}
  deltay[p]:= 75 ' jump v_i

  repeat until deltay[p] <= -deltay[p] and heightOffGround[p] <= 0 'max fall speed: -deltay[p]
    deltay[p] -= 15 'fall accel;
    case_fast deltay[p]
      -100..-1 : Momot:=MMRISE
      0 : Momot:=MMFLOAT
      1..100 : Momot:=MMFALL
    waitms(FrameTime*1)
  deltay[p]:=0 'Since landed, no longer falling
  Momot:= MMCROUCH
  waitms(1*FrameTime) 'landing lag time
  Momot:=MM_I
  playerState[4+9*p]:=false     'Once both conditions met, momot has landed

pub MomotPunch()
  if PunchRight == true       'Variable used to alternate which punching motion is used'
    case Momot
      100 : Momot:= 111                'Run through Momot's Punch Right sprites' (similar to motion logic from demo)
      111 : Momot:= 112
      112 : Momot:= 113
      113 : Momot:= 114
      114 : Momot:= 100
        PunchRight:= false             'Set PunchRight to false to punch left next time'
        playerState[5]:= false          'Set Punching flag to false to stop punching'
  else
    case Momot                          'Run through Momot's Punch left sprites' (similar to motion logic from demo)
      100 : Momot:= 116
      116 : Momot:= 117
      117 : Momot:= 118
      118 : Momot:= 119
      119 : Momot:= 100
        PunchRight:= true               'Set PunchRight to true to punch right next time'
        playerState[5] := false        'Set Punching flag to false to stop punching'

pub MomotKick()
  case Momot
      100 : Momot:= 122               'Run through Momot'Kick sprites' (similar to motion logic from demo)
      122 : Momot:= 123
      123 : Momot:= 124
      124 : Momot:= 125
      125 : Momot:= 126
      126 : Momot:= 100
        playerState[6]:= false

pub MomotBlock()
  if (data[7].[4] == 0)      'CREDIT: Gemini -- AI Helped rewrite this method when implementing two playable characters'
    Momot := 115
    playerState[7] := true          'Set Momot's sprite to blocking when blocking state is on'
  else
    Momot := 100
    playerState[7] := false          'Reset Momot's sprite when not blocking'


pub GarnerMotion() | p
  p:=1
   repeat
    if playerState[4+9*p]                 'Jumping Logic'
      case_fast p
        0 : MomotJump()
        1 : GarnerJump()


    if playerState[2+9*p]==false            'Check to see if Cog 0 has set the MomotMoving flag to be true or false
      {Idle State -- Make eye movement happer}
      Garner:= GGIC
      repeat until playerState[2+9*p]==true 'Repeat until moving

    if playerState[2+9*p]==true
    {Moving animation}
        case Garner
          GGIC : Garner:= 5                          'Run through Garner's walking sprites'
          5 : Garner:= 6
          6 : Garner:= 7
          7 : Garner:= GGIC
        waitms(FrameTime#> 6*FrameTime/deltax[p] <#4*FrameTime)



pub GarnerJump() | p
  'deals with the Garner Jumping animation and speed
  p:= 1 'For Garner
  Garner:= GGCROUCH
  waitms(2*FrameTime) 'Jumpsquat time
  'if {short vs. full hop; read button again}
  deltay[p]:= 60 ' jump v_i
  Garner:= GGLAND
  waitms(1*FrameTime) 'Jumpsquat time
  repeat until deltay[p] <= -deltay[p]+50 and heightOffGround[p] <= 0 'max fall speed: -deltay[p]
    deltay[p] -= 20 'fall accel;
    case_fast deltay[p]
      -100..-1 :
        case Garner
          GGLAND : Garner:= GGJUMP
          GGJUMP : Garner:= GGLAND
          other : Garner:= GGLAND
      0 : Garner:=GGJUMP
      1..100 : Garner:=GGFALL
    waitms(FrameTime*1)
  deltay[p]:=0 'Since landed, no longer falling
  Garner:= GGCROUCH
  waitms(2*FrameTime) 'landing lag time
  Garner:= GGIC
  playerState[4+9*p]:=false     'Once both conditions met, player has landed

pub GarnerBaseAttack()
  case Garner
    GGIC : Garner:=  GGINSTRUCT
    case playerState[10]    'Adjust the Location of the Sprite Depending on Garner's Rotation'
       0 : debug(`screen set (`(playerPos[x+4] + 64), `(playerPos[y+4])) sprite (`(GGAtt), 0, 3, 255)
       1 : debug(`screen set (`(playerPos[x+4] - 64), `(playerPos[y+4])) sprite (`(GGAtt), 1, 3, 255)
     case GGAtt
        25 : GGAtt := 26    'Flicker Between two base attack sprites'
        26 : GGAtt := 25
    GGINSTRUCT : Garner := GGIC
      playerState[14]:=false   'Set Base Attack Flag back to false to stop attacking'

pub GarnerHeavyAttack()
  case Garner
    GGIC : Garner:=  GGINSTRUCT
     case playerState[10] 'Adjust the Location of the Sprite Depending on Garner's Rotation'
       0 : debug(`screen set (`(playerPos[x+4] + 64), `(playerPos[y+4])) sprite (`(GGHAtt), 0, 3, 255)
       1 : debug(`screen set (`(playerPos[x+4] - 64), `(playerPos[y+4])) sprite (`(GGHAtt), 1, 3, 255)
     case GGHAtt
        27 : GGHAtt := 28     'Flicker Between two heavy attack sprites'
        28 : GGHAtt := 27
    GGINSTRUCT : Garner := GGIC
      playerState[15]:=false    'Set Heavy Attack Flag back to false to stop attacking'

pub GarnerBlock()
  if (data[15].[4] == 0)
    Garner := 10                  'Same logic and credit as Momot's Blocking Method'
    playerState[16] := true
  else
    Garner := GGIC
    playerState[16] := false

pub DefineCollisionAreas() | i      'Define all the collision areas for all parts of the game'

  playerPos[x]:=MOMOT_INIT[x]                        'X Position'
  playerPos[y]:=MOMOT_INIT[y]                        'Y Position'       'Momot's Position (and Attack) Collision Area
  playerz[0]:=MOMOT_INIT[y]                           'Width'
  playerPos[width]:=MOMOT_INIT[width]                 'Height'
  playerPos[height]:=MOMOT_INIT[height]

  playerPos[x+4]:=GARNER_INIT[x]                                        'Garner's Position Collision Area'
  playerPos[y+4]:=GARNER_INIT[y]
  playerPos[width+4]:=GARNER_INIT[width]
  playerPos[height+4]:=GARNER_INIT[height]
  playerz[1]:=GARNER_INIT[y]
                                                                        'Bullet Bill's Damage and Health Collision Area'
  BulletB[0]:=700
  BulletB[1]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
  BulletB[2]:=64
  BulletB[3]:=64

                                                                      'Garner's Base Attack Collision Area'
  GGBATT[0]:=GARNER_INIT[x]+80
  GGBATT[1]:=GARNER_INIT[y]-48
  GGBATT[2]:=80
  GGBATT[3]:=48

  GGHeATT[0]:=GARNER_INIT[x]+80                                     'Garner's Heavy Attack Collision Area'
  GGHeATT[1]:=GARNER_INIT[y]-32
  GGHeATT[2]:=80
  GGHeATT[3]:=24
                                                                    'Red Pikmin's Damage and Health Collision Area'
  Pikmin[0]:=750
  Pikmin[1]:=125
  Pikmin[2]:=32
  Pikmin[3]:=90

  Pikmin[4]:=750                                                   'Yellow Pikmin's Damage and Health Collitions
  Pikmin[5]:=125
  Pikmin[6]:=32
  Pikmin[7]:=90

  Pikmin[8]:=750                                                  'Blue Pikmin's Damage and Health Collitions
  Pikmin[9]:=125
  Pikmin[10]:=32
  Pikmin[11]:=90
                                                                   'Momot's Defensive Hitbox'
  HitBoxes[x]:=playerPos[x]+16
  HitBoxes[y]:=playerPos[y]
  HitBoxes[width]:=64
  HitBoxes[height]:=MOMOT_INIT[height]
                                                                   'Garner's Defensive Hitbox
  HitBoxes[x+4]:=playerPos[x+4]+16
  HitBoxes[y+4]:=playerPos[y+4]
  HitBoxes[width+4]:=64
  HitBoxes[height+4]:=GARNER_INIT[height]


  HealthBoost[0]:=RPosX
  HealthBoost[1]:=RPosY
  HealthBoost[2]:=48
  HealthBoost[3]:=48



pub CheckCollision(Box1address,Box2address) : CollisionState      'CREDIT: This algorithm is based on the one described at https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Games/Techniques/2D_collision_detection
  CollisionState~                                                 'Initialize CollisionState as zero (which is the same as "false")
  if long[Box1address]<(long[Box2address]+long[Box2address][2]) and {
            }(long[Box1address]+long[Box1address][2])>long[Box2address] and {
                 } long[Box1address][1]>(long[Box2address][1]-long[Box2address][3]) and {
                      } (long[Box1address][1]-long[Box1address][3])<(long[Box2address][1])
    CollisionState:=true                                          'If a collision is detected set the method's return value to "true" (which is -1 or 32 ones in binary)
  else
    CollisionState:=false

  if CollisionDebugMode==true 'Show red bounding boxes around the characters and to display an alert on the screen whenever there's a collision.
                              'Note this significantly slows down your main loop, so only use this feature for a brief time while debugging specific problems i.e., don't keep this active throughout your entire game making process!
    debug(`screen set `(long[Box1address]) `(long[Box1address][1]) red line `(long[Box1address]+long[Box1address][2])) `(long[Box1address][1]))
    debug(`screen set `(long[Box1address]+long[Box1address][2])) `(long[Box1address][1])) red line `(long[Box1address]+long[Box1address][2])) `(long[Box1address][1]-long[Box1address][3]))
    debug(`screen set `(long[Box1address]+long[Box1address][2])) `(long[Box1address][1]-long[Box1address][3])) red line `(long[Box1address])) `(long[Box1address][1]-long[Box1address][3]))
    debug(`screen set `(long[Box1address])) `(long[Box1address][1]-long[Box1address][3])) red line `(long[Box1address]) `(long[Box1address][1]))

    debug(`screen set `(long[Box2address]) `(long[Box2address][1]) red line `(long[Box2address]+long[Box2address][2])) `(long[Box2address][1]))
    debug(`screen set `(long[Box2address]+long[Box2address][2])) `(long[Box2address][1])) red line `(long[Box2address]+long[Box2address][2])) `(long[Box2address][1]-long[Box2address][3]))
    debug(`screen set `(long[Box2address]+long[Box2address][2])) `(long[Box2address][1]-long[Box2address][3])) red line `(long[Box2address])) `(long[Box2address][1]-long[Box2address][3]))
    debug(`screen set `(long[Box2address])) `(long[Box2address][1]-long[Box2address][3])) red line `(long[Box2address]) `(long[Box2address][1]))

    if CollisionState==true
      debug(`screen set 400 330 red text 50 'Collision!!!')

pub PauseGame(player)                                   'If player presses the Select button on the controller, the game should pause until the player presses Select again. Note that this only pauses your main game loop on Cog 0. Other cogs will still be running as usual (which could continue to change some global variables).
  debug(`screen set 400 330 red text 50 '<P`(player) PAUSED>')
  'debug(`term1 'L Stick P1= `(data[0]) `(data[2])',10)
  debug(`screen update `dly(1000))                'Force game window to update (in order to display the "<PAUSED>" text) then wait/delay 1 second
  ReadController(1)                                'Jump down to the ReadController method to read/update the controller's current user input data via the I2C interface
  repeat until data[6].[4]==0                     'Wait for the player to press the + button a second time to un-pause the game
    ReadController(1)                              'Jump down to the ReadController method to read/update the controller's current user input data via the I2C interface
    waitms(100)                                   'Slow things down during this paused condition while just waiting for the usert to un-pause the game
  repeat until data[6].[4]==1                     'Wait for the player to release the + button (otherwise another pause condition may be immediately initiated again)
    ReadController(1)                              'Update the controller button data
  StartTime:=getct()                              'Re-record current system clock counter (so that the >100ms warning isn't displayed when this frame finishes)


pub DrawGame()                  'Responsible for rendering the sprites to the debug screen so that the game is visible
    DrawBackground()
    DrawActors()
    if GameWon == false and GameLost == false       'Check if GameOver conditions are active before activating enemies'
      DrawLevel(CurrentLevel)

pub DrawBackground() | i,j

  repeat i from 0 to 800 step 64                               'Draw Brick Wall and Floor Sprites (similar to floor tiles in demo)'
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 64) sprite (200, 0, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 128) sprite (200, 3, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 192) sprite (200, 0, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 256) sprite (200, 3, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 320) sprite (201, 0, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 384) sprite (201, 0, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 448) sprite (201, 0, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 512) sprite (201, 0, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 576) sprite (201, 0, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 640) sprite (201, 0, 2))
      debug(`screen set (`(i), 704) sprite (201, 0, 2))

  {Health Bar Names}

  debug(`screen set 88 600 blue text 18 'Momot')
  debug(`screen set 88 552 blue text 18 'Garner')

  {Displays Current Level}

  if GameWon == false and GameLost == false
    debug(`screen set 400 400 red text 48 'Level `(CurrentLevel)')

  {Displays Health Bars}

  if HealthBar[0] > 0
    debug(`screen set 88 576 color $DB1818 box 144 24)
    debug(`screen set `(16+(HealthBar[0] / 2)) 576 color $1BDB18 box `(HealthBar[0]) 24)     'CREDIT: GEMINI -- Used AI to figure out how to make the healthbar go from left to right'
  else
    debug(`screen set 88 576 red text 18 'You Died...')
                                                                                            'These two if statements display the healthbars of the two players which are replaced by the message,
  if HealthBar[1] > 0                                                                         '"You died..." when the players run out of health
    debug(`screen set 88 528 color $DB1818 box 144 24)
    if pvpState == true
      debug(`screen set `(16+(HealthBar[1] / 2)) 528 color $1818DB box `(HealthBar[1]) 24)   'Makes Garner Health Blue when PVP active'
    else                                                                           '"You died..." when the players run out of health
      debug(`screen set `(16+(HealthBar[1] / 2)) 528 color $1BDB18 box `(HealthBar[1]) 24)
  else
    debug(`screen set 88 528 red text 18 'You Died...')

  {Display Winning Message}
  if GameWon
     debug(`screen set 400 560 red text 48 'You Win!!')
     debug(`screen set 400 496 red text 24 'You saved the Mech Building and')
     debug(`screen set 400 464 red text 24 'the P2 Chips from the Pikmin!!')
     debug(`screen set 400 432 red text 20 'If you would like to play again P1 press START!!')

  {Display Losing Message}
  if GameLost
     debug(`screen set 400 560 red text 48 'Game Over!!')
     debug(`screen set 400 496 red text 24 'The Pikmin took over the Mech Building')
     debug(`screen set 400 464 red text 24 'and destroyed all the P2 Chips!!')
     debug(`screen set 400 432 red text 20 'If you would like to play again P1 press START!!')

  debug(`screen set (upper-left_X_coordinate, upper-left_Y_coordinate) sprite (SpriteNumber, Rotation, ScalingFactor, SpriteOpacity))

pub SpawnActors()
    {Player Initial States}
    Momot := 100
    playerState[3]:=255
    Garner := 0
    playerState[12]:=255
    playerPos[x]:=MOMOT_INIT[x]
    playerPos[y]:=MOMOT_INIT[y]
    playerPos[width]:=MOMOT_INIT[width]                   '
    playerPos[height]:=MOMOT_INIT[height]
    playerPos[x+4]:=GARNER_INIT[x]
    playerPos[y+4]:=GARNER_INIT[y]
    playerPos[width+4]:=GARNER_INIT[width]
    playerPos[height+4]:=GARNER_INIT[height]
    heightOffGround[0]:=0
    heightOffGround[1]:=0
    HealthBar[0]:=144
    HealthBar[1]:=144
    PunchRight := true
    GGAtt:=25
    GGHAtt:= 27

    {Game Initial States}
    KillCounter:=0
    KillCounterCheck:=7
    RandomCheck:= getrnd()+//5
    RPosX := 50 + getrnd()+//600   'Set the HealthBoost X Position to a Random Number Between 50 and 650'
    RPosY := 50 + getrnd()+//200   'Set the HealthBoost Y Position to a Random Number Between 50 and 250'

pub SpawnEnemies()
    {Enemy Initial States}
    BulletHealth:=255
    BulletRot:=1
    Pikmin[0]:=750
    Pikmin[1]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
    PikminHealth[0]:=255
    Pikmin[4]:=750
    Pikmin[5]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
    PikminHealth[1]:=255
    HealthBoostGranted := false

pub DrawActors()                'Draw all of the Characters on screen that change (players, enemies, items, health status)
    {DRAWING SPRITES}
            'Sprites's: X position,  Y position   Sprite's: image #,  rotation, scaling, opacity

    {Momot}
    if HealthBar[0] > 0
      debug(`screen set (`(playerPos[x]), `(playerPos[y])) sprite (`(Momot), `(playerState[1]), 3, `(playerState[3]))

    {Garner}
    if HealthBar[1] > 0
      debug(`screen set (`(playerPos[x+4]), `(playerPos[y+4])) sprite (`(Garner), `(playerState[10]), 3, `(playerState[12]))

    {Health Boost -- Only sometimes active on Level 2}
    if (CurrentLevel == 2 and HealthBoostGranted == false and SpawnBoost == true)
      if (HealthBoostGranted == false)
        debug(`screen set `(RPosX), `(RPosY)) sprite (133, 0, 3, 255))



pub DrawLevel(level)    'Method that spawns enemies for each different level'
  case_fast level
    1 : {Level One}
      {Bullet Bill}
      if (BulletHealth > 16)                                                                               'Draw Enemy while their Health (opacity) is over 16'
        debug(`screen set `(BulletB[0]), `(BulletB[1])) sprite (132, `(BulletRot), 4, `(BulletHealth))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1  'Update Kill Counter'
        if KillCounter < 10           'Respawn the Enemy while the Kill Counter is below a certain threshhold'
          BulletHealth:= 255
          BulletB[0]:=700              'Respawn by resetting enemy properties'
          BulletB[1]:= 50 + getrnd()+//200  'Spawn the Enemy in a Random Y Position'
          BulletRot:= 1
      {Red Pikmin}
      if (PikminHealth[0] > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[0]), `(Pikmin[1])) sprite (29, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[0]))
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[0]), `(Pikmin[1]-48)) sprite (31, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[0]))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 10
          PikminHealth[0] := 255
          Pikmin[0]:=750
          Pikmin[1]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
      {Yellow Pikmin}
      if (PikminHealth[1] > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[4]), `(Pikmin[5])) sprite (33, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[1]))
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[4]), `(Pikmin[5]-48)) sprite (37, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[1]))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 10
          PikminHealth[1] := 255
          Pikmin[4]:=750
          Pikmin[5]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
    2 : {Level Two (Same Logic as Level 1 with Different Enemies}
      {Blue Pikmin}
      if (PikminHealth[2] > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[8]), `(Pikmin[9])) sprite (35, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[2]))
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[8]), `(Pikmin[9]-48)) sprite (39, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[2]))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 15
          PikminHealth[2]:= 255
          Pikmin[8]:=750
          Pikmin[9]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
          {Red Pikmin}
      if (PikminHealth[0] > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[0]), `(Pikmin[1])) sprite (29, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[0]))
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[0]), `(Pikmin[1]-48)) sprite (31, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[0]))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 10
          PikminHealth[0] := 255
          Pikmin[0]:=750
          Pikmin[1]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
          {Yellow Pikmin}
      if (PikminHealth[1] > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[4]), `(Pikmin[5])) sprite (33, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[1]))
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[4]), `(Pikmin[5]-48)) sprite (37, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[1]))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 10
          PikminHealth[1] := 255
          Pikmin[4]:=750
          Pikmin[5]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
    3 : {Level Three (Same Logic as Level 1 and 2 with Different Enemies}
       {Blue Pikmin}
      if (PikminHealth[2] > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[8]), `(Pikmin[9])) sprite (35, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[2]))
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[8]), `(Pikmin[9]-48)) sprite (39, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[2]))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 15
          PikminHealth[2]:= 255
          Pikmin[8]:=750
          Pikmin[9]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
          {Red Pikmin}
      if (PikminHealth[0] > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[0]), `(Pikmin[1])) sprite (29, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[0]))
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[0]), `(Pikmin[1]-48)) sprite (31, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[0]))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 10
          PikminHealth[0] := 255
          Pikmin[0]:=750
          Pikmin[1]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
          {Yellow Pikmin}
      if (PikminHealth[1] > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[4]), `(Pikmin[5])) sprite (33, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[1]))
        debug(`screen set `(Pikmin[4]), `(Pikmin[5]-48)) sprite (37, 0, 3, `(PikminHealth[1]))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 10
          PikminHealth[1] := 255
          Pikmin[4]:=750
          Pikmin[5]:=50 + getrnd()+//200
          {Bullet Bill}
      if (BulletHealth > 16)
        debug(`screen set `(BulletB[0]), `(BulletB[1])) sprite (132, `(BulletRot), 4, `(BulletHealth))
      else
        KillCounter:=KillCounter + 1
        if KillCounter < 10
          BulletHealth:= 255
          BulletB[0]:=700
          BulletB[1]:= 50 + getrnd()+//200
          BulletRot:= 1


pub ShowInstructions() | i
  debug(`term Instructions pos 140 100 size 75 24 textsize 12 color black white backcolor white)  'Create a new debug terminal window called called "Instructions" at x=140 y=100 on the PC screen (overlaid on plot window)                                                                                            ' that is 75 spaces wide by 10 lines deep with text color=black on white with white background and font size 12
                                                                                                  ' that is 75 text spaces wide by 24 lines deep with text color=black on white with white background and font size 12
  repeat i from 0 to 1                           'This is a demo of how to point to different string addresses in a "for" loop
    PrintStr(@@StringAddress[i])                 'Print string who's starting address is at the specified memory location (Note: You must use two @ symbols to pass the address of a string like this!)
  debug(`Instructions 2 15 3 10)                 'Set cursor's column to 30 and row to be 10 (2=set column command, 3=set row command -> see Text Terminal section of Spin2 Programming documnent)
  PrintStr(@string2)                             'Print string who's starting address is at the memory location named string2
  repeat until data[6].[2]==0                    'Wait until Start button is pressed on the Wii controller
    ReadController(1)                             'Update data bytes from the Wii Controller
    waitms(100)                                  'No need to do this too quickly as we're dealing with human-scale speeds and don't want to clober the I2C interface or waste electricity
  debug(`Instructions clear)                     'Clear entire terminal window and reset cursor to home (upper left)
  debug(`Instructions 2 33 3 5)                  'Set cursor's column to 33 and row to be 5
  PrintStr(@string3)                             'Print string who's starting address is at the memory location named string3
  waitms(750)
  debug(`Instructions close)                     'Close this debug text terminal window

pub PrintStr(strAddress)                        'Print a string of characters that starts at a specified memory address (with no new line afterward)
  repeat (strsize(strAddress))                   'Repeat once for each character in the string (strsize returns the total length of the string up to its terminating 0
    if byte[strAddress]==13                      'Check to see if the current character is code=13, which indicates a line feed and carriage return
      debug(`debugWindow 13)                    'Create a new line and carriage return (i.e., return cursor to the far left)             `
      strAddress++                               'Increment the string address index pointer by 1 to move on to the next character in the string
    else
      debug(`debugWindow `(byte[strAddress++])) 'Print the last character and increment the address pointer

dat
string0       byte "Mario Demo Game Instructions:", 13, 13, 0    'Define a zero-terminated string of characters/bytes starting at memory address "string0" Use character=13 to add new lines (2 in this case)
string1       byte {                                             'Here's an example of how you can define one long string across multiple lines
} "Use the Wii Controller's left joystick to move Mario around.", 13, "If Mario collides with Goomba, he becomes a ghost, but if Mario finds and  touches the FireFlower he is reborn.", 13, 13, {
}"Hint: What happens if you press both the A and ZR buttons at the same time while Mario is standing on top of the topmost question mark? ;-)",0
string2       byte "---> Press the Start Button to play...",0
string3       byte "HAVE FUN!!!",0

